J_{i-} = J_{i1} - J_{i2} = \dot{x}_{i+}\rho_{-} + \dot{x}_{i-}\rho_{+}
\end{array}
\end{eqnarray}
We can solve the equations of motion for $A_{i\pm}$ in the Lorentz gauge. We assume that initial conditions are given for fields $\phi(t_i)$ and $A(t_i)$ as well as their first order spatial and temporal derivatives. These initial conditions could be associated with the initial conditions for $\phi_{+}$ and $A_{i+}$ in their physical limits.  
On the other hand, $\phi_{-}$ and $A_{i-}$ satisfy the equality condition at the final time given by

